[0.001, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f<?php\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[96mdefined\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'BASEPATH'\u001b[m\u000f) OR \u001b[0;10;1m\u000fexit\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'No direct script access allowed'\u001b[m\u000f);\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n/*\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| DATABASE CONNECTIVITY SETTINGS\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| This file will contain the settings needed to access your database.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| For complete instructions please consult the 'Database Connection'\u001b[K\r\n| page of the User Guide.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| EXPLANATION OF VARIABLES\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dsn']      The full DSN string describe a connection to the database.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['hostname'] The hostname of your database server.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['username'] 'arteri'\u001b[K\r\n|       ['password'] '123'\u001b[K\r\n|       ['database'] 'arteri'\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dbdriver'] The database driver. e.g.: mysqli.\u001b[K\r\n|                       Currently supported:\u001b[K\r\n|                                cubrid, ibase, mssql, mysql, mysqli, oci8,\u001b[K\r\n|                                odbc, pdo, postgre, sqlite, sqlite3, sqlsrv\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dbprefix'] You can add an optional prefix, which will be added\u001b[K\r\n|                                to the table name when using the  Query Builder class\u001b[K\r\n|       ['pconnect'] TRUE/FALSE - Whether to use a persistent connection\u001b[K\r\n|       ['db_debug'] TRUE/FALSE - Whether database errors should be displayed.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['cache_on'] TRUE/FALSE - Enables/disables query caching\u001b[K\r\n|       ['cachedir'] The path to the folder where cache files should be stored\u001b[K\r\n|       ['char_set'] The character set used in communicating with the database\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dbcollat'] The character collation used in communicating with the database\u001b[K\r\n|                                NOTE: For MySQL and MySQLi databases, this setting is only used\u001b[K\r\n|                                as a backup if your server is running PHP < 5.2.3 or MySQL < 5.0.7\u001b[K\r\n|                                (and in table creation queries made with DB Forge).\u001b[K\r\n|                                There is an incompatibility in PHP with mysql_real_escape_string() which\u001b[K\r\n|                                can make your site vulnerable to SQL injection if you are using a\u001b[K\r\n|                                multi-byte character set and are running versions lower than these.\u001b[K\r\n|                                Sites using Latin-1 or UTF-8 database character set and collation are unaffected.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['swap_pre'] A default table prefix that should be swapped with the dbprefix\u001b[K\r\n|       ['encrypt']  Whether or not to use an encrypted connection.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n|                       'mysql' (deprecated), 'sqlsrv' and 'pdo/sqlsrv' drivers accept TRUE/FALSE\u001b[K\r\n|                       'mysqli' and 'pdo/mysql' drivers accept an array with the following options:\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f/usr/share/nginx/html/arteri/application/config/database.php                                                                                            1,1            Top\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[J\u001b[?112c\u001b[?112c\u001b[H<?php\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[96mdefined\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'BASEPATH'\u001b[m\u000f) OR \u001b[0;10;1m\u000fexit\u001b[m\u000f(\u001b[92m'No direct script access allowed'\u001b[m\u000f);\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n/*\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| DATABASE CONNECTIVITY SETTINGS\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| This file will contain the settings needed to access your database.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| For complete instructions please consult the 'Database Connection'\u001b[K\r\n| page of the User Guide.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n| EXPLANATION OF VARIABLES\u001b[K\r\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dsn']      The full DSN string describe a connection to the database.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['hostname'] The hostname of your database server.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['username'] 'arteri'\u001b[K\r\n|       ['password'] '123'\u001b[K\r\n|       ['"]
[0.000, "o", "database'] 'arteri'\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dbdriver'] The database driver. e.g.: mysqli.\u001b[K\r\n|                       Currently supported:\u001b[K\r\n|                                cubrid, ibase, mssql, mysql, mysqli, oci8,\u001b[K\r\n|                                odbc, pdo, postgre, sqlite, sqlite3, sqlsrv\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dbprefix'] You can add an optional prefix, which will be added\u001b[K\r\n|                                to the table name when using the  Query Builder class\u001b[K\r\n|       ['pconnect'] TRUE/FALSE - Whether to use a persistent connection\u001b[K\r\n|       ['db_debug'] TRUE/FALSE - Whether database errors should be displayed.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['cache_on'] TRUE/FALSE - Enables/disables query caching\u001b[K\r\n|       ['cachedir'] The path to the folder where cache files should be stored\u001b[K\r\n|       ['char_set'] The character set used in communicating with the database\u001b[K\r\n|       ['dbcollat'] The character collation used in communicating with the database\u001b[K\r\n|                                NOTE: For MySQL and MySQLi databases, this setting is only used\u001b[K\r\n|                                as a backup if your server is running PHP < 5.2.3 or MySQL < 5.0.7\u001b[K\r\n|                                (and in table creation queries made with DB Forge).\u001b[K\r\n|                                There is an incompatibility in PHP with mysql_real_escape_string() which\u001b[K\r\n|                                can make your site vulnerable to SQL injection if you are using a\u001b[K\r\n|                                multi-byte character set and are running versions lower than these.\u001b[K\r\n|                                Sites using Latin-1 or UTF-8 database character set and collation are unaffected.\u001b[K\r\n|       ['swap_pre'] A default table prefix that should be swapped with the dbprefix\u001b[K\r\n|       ['encrypt']  Whether or not to use an encrypted connection.\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n|                       'mysql' (deprecated), 'sqlsrv' and 'pdo/sqlsrv' drivers accept TRUE/FALSE\u001b[K\r\n|                       'mysqli' and 'pdo/mysql' drivers accept an array with the following options:\u001b[K\r\n|\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f/usr/share/nginx/html/arteri/application/config/database.php                                                                                            1,1            Top\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[J\u001b[H\u001b[?25h\u001bP+q4D73\u001b\\"]
